Responsibilities:

Work closely with the research scientists and support a small team of engineers, primarily, you will take charge of all technical engineering needs for R&D project plans, manage project status and overall process in achieving project goals:
Administering the project and monitoring all engineering work;
Finish architect design for molecular diagnosis medical devices including machine work-flow and procedure layout to identify key steps for completeing a sample-in-result-out test, control layout & AP specifications;
Effectively manage problems throughout prototyping phase, e.g. identify and troubleshoot technical issues;
Industrial design to include 3D hardware structure data, BOM and drawings of all modules and components, finalize system integration including system architecture and liquid level detection control;
Pre-clinical evaluations, and transfer of product to manufacturing;
Complete project reports
Liaise with vendors and external research organizations to carry out the strategic partnerships;
Develop and strengthen the engineering team.

Requirements:

Master Degrees or above in bioengineering, mechatronics, mechanics, electronics, optical and related disciplines;
Over 5-10years relevant project management and leadership experience in the development of medical devices, especially in the application and commercialization of research findings;
Strong technical competencies in design, debug and problem solving;
Ability to formulate scientific hypothesis and demonstrate technical proficiency, scientific creativity,
Able to collaborate with others while maintain independent thought;
Detail-minded, committed, can-do attitude and can work under pressure;
Excellent communications and interpersonal skills;
Good command of the English and Chinese languages, written and spoken, including Cantonese and Mandarin.
If you are passionate, driven and looking for a new and exciting opportunity within a successful and growing company, this may be the right role for you.
